http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/YSRC-MP-wants-more-trains-to-stop-at-Ongole/article13988169.ece

YSR Congress Whip in Parliament Y.V. Subba Reddy on Thursday demanded that the railway authorities must initiate measures to ensure that more south-bound trains made halt at Ongole railway station, for the benefit of commuters.In a representation to South Central Railway Manager Ravindra Gupta pointed that people from other states including Kerala, Bihar, Himanchal Pradesh and Rajasthan had made Prakasam district their second home.He sought stoppage of the Kerala Express, Jodhpur Express, Jaipur Express, Pondicherry Express at Ongole.